A tycoon involved in a dispute over land in Watamu is blaming politicians for his misfortunes.Last week, his two vehicles and an ambulance were torched by residents. This was after they alleged police and goons demolished a building at a disputed land, which led to the chaos. Habib Mohamed said he lost Sh6 million.Mohamed said he has never grabbed land. The tycoon said the land in dispute is prime and it is valued at Sh5 million and he owns it.Mohamed said there were demolition orders from the court and before they were executed, he consulted elders and religious leaders to convince the woman occupying the land to negotiate with him. &ldquo;But before that I went to local leaders, but still their efforts to convince her were unsuccessful,&rsquo;&rsquo; he said .